  <tr>
    <td class="txt">We are at present no longer accepting applications for membership, that does
    NOT mean you can't still apply, just don't expect a
    response on your application any time soon. This is a
    short term closure of applications while we reshuffle the
    guilds internal mechanics.<br><br>
    To apply, goto our Forums section, and leave a message on the
    Applications board, put your name class, level and time
    zone in in the application header. Then a brief
    description of why you want to join, what experience you
    have (in brief). etc.<br><br>
    Your application will then be moved to the private Application
    area, where existing members will vote on your
    application. Once your application has positive feedback and 3 officers have
      voted yes,
    a decision will be made. If the
    decision is positive you will be guilded for 1 month.
    during which time you are expected to group with other
    guild members wherever possible. During this period you will <b>not</b> be
      able to bid on any items against existing members, although you will still
      accrue <a href="elp.asp" class="link">Event Lotto Points (ELP)</a>. After this 1 month
    period, a re-poll on your application is taken, where we
    will decide if we wish to offer you a permanent position
    in the Dark Templars. If your application was declined you
    will be notified by an Officer and given the reasons why,
    where possible. (1st May 2002).</td>
  </tr>
</table>

